==== Convex sets and convex components in order theory ====

A subset formula_71 of the preordered set formula_56 is (order-)convex if for every formula_73 and every formula_74 we have formula_75 Unlike in the case of the real line, a convex set of a preordered set need not be an interval. For example, in the totally ordered set formula_76 of rational numbers, the set
