Then xax−1

= ( 1 2 3 ) ( 2 3 ) ( 3 2 1 ) = ( 3 1 )

= ( 3 1 ) is Conjugate of ( 2 3 )

==Properties==

* The identity element is always the only element in its class, that is formula_35
* If formula_7 is abelian then formula_37 for all formula_38, i.e. formula_39 for all formula_21 (and the converse is also true: if all conjugacy classes are singletons then formula_7 is abelian).
* If two elements formula_8 belong to the same conjugacy class (that is, if they are conjugate), then they have the same order. More generally, every statement about formula_1 can be translated into a statement about formula_44 because the map formula_45 is an automorphism of formula_7 called an inner automorphism. See the next property for an example.
* If formula_1 and formula_2 are conjugate, then so are their powers formula_49 and formula_50 (Proof: if formula_51 then formula_52) Thus taking th powers gives a map on conjugacy classes, and one may consider which conjugacy classes are in its preimage. For example, in the symmetric group, the square of an element of type (3)(2) (a 3-cycle and a 2-cycle) is an element of type (3), therefore one of the power-up classes of (3) is the class (3)(2) (where formula_1 is a power-up class of formula_49).
* An element formula_21 lies in the center formula_56 of formula_7 if and only if its conjugacy class has only one element, formula_1 itself. More generally, if formula_59 denotes the of formula_60 i.e., the subgroup consisting of all elements formula_3 such that formula_62 then the index formula_63 is equal to the number of elements in the conjugacy class of formula_1 (by the orbit-stabilizer theorem).
* Take formula_65 and let formula_66 be the distinct integers which appear as lengths of cycles in the cycle type of formula_67 (including 1-cycles). Let formula_68 be the number of cycles of length formula_69 in formula_67 for each formula_71 (so that formula_72). Then the number of conjugates of formula_67 is:formula_74

==Conjugacy as group action==

For any two elements formula_75 let
formula_76
This defines a group action of formula_7 on formula_78 The orbits of this action are the conjugacy classes, and the stabilizer of a given element is the element&#x27;s centralizer.

Similarly, we can define a group action of formula_7 on the set of all subsets of formula_80 by writing
