where formula_100 is the centralizer of the element formula_101 Observing that each element of the center formula_56 forms a conjugacy class containing just itself gives rise to the class equation:
formula_103
where the sum is over a representative element from each conjugacy class that is not in the center.

Knowledge of the divisors of the group order formula_104 can often be used to gain information about the order of the center or of the conjugacy classes.

