==Legacy==
In the Soviet Union, streets named after Lysenko existed in several cities, such as Krasnoturyinsk.

Arkady and Boris Strugatsky cited Lysenko as the inspiration for the character of from their 1965 satirical science fantasy novel &quot;Monday Begins on Saturday&quot;:
Lysenko’s ideas have been attracting a renewed following in contemporary Russia, linked to a strain of Russian nationalism that views “Western” ideas and mainstream science with suspicion.

