===Patents===
Below is a sampling of U.S. patents for inventions by George Westinghouse. Many of the same inventions were also patented in foreign countries, including Austria, Australia, Canada, Denmark, France, Germany, Great Britain, Spain, and Switzerland. Many other patents were filed in the names of his companies or various of his engineers.
* , 1862, grain and seed winnowers; patent awarded to father George Westinghouse Sr. 
* , 1865, improvement in rotary steam-engines; 1st patent awarded to George Westinghouse Jr.
* , 1867, improved railroad switch and car replacer; device to help put derailed train car back on track
* , 1868, improved railway frog; device for switching trains between tracks
* , 1869, improvement in steam-power-brake devices; the air brake

* , 1870, improvements in steam engine and pump
* , 1870, improvement in atmospheric car-brake pipes
* , 1873, improvement in steam and air brakes
* , 1873, improvement in steam-power-brake couplings
* , 1874, improvement in valves for fluid brake-pipes
* , 1875, pneumatic pump
* , 1879, improvement in auxiliary telephon exchanges
* , 1879, automatic telephone switch for connecting local lines by means of main line
* , 1879, improvement in fluid-pressure brake apparatus
* , 1881, interlocking switch and signal apparatus
* , 1883, fluid-pressure regulator
* , 1884, system for conveying and utilizing gas under pressure
* , 1884, means for detecting leaks in gas mains
* , 1885, system for the protection of railroad-tracks and gas-pipe lines
* , 1885, means for detecting and carrying off leakage from gas mains
* , 1886, system of electrical distribution
* , 1886, induction coil
* , 1887, commutator for dynamo electric machines 
* , 1887, electrical converter; a type of transformer
* , 1887, system of electrical distribution
* , 1888, electric meter (with Philip Lange)
* , 1889, system of electrical distribution
* , 1889, fluid-meter
* , 1890, fluid-pressure automatic brake mechanism
* , 1890, alternating current electric meter
* , 1890, fluid-pressure automatic brake
* , 1890, electric railway system
* , 1891, switch and signal apparatus
* , 1891, pipe-coupling
* , 1893, draw-gear apparatus for cars
* , 1893, conduit electric railway
* , 1895, incandescent electric lamp
* , 1895, electric railway
* , 1897, current-collecting device for railway-vehicles
